  "prompt": "What is TRATAK YOGA?",
  "response": "Trataka Yoga is a traditional yogic practice of concentrated gazing, primarily focusing on a single point or object. Here are key details about Trataka:\n\n1. Basic Definition:\n- A meditation technique involving steady, unblinking gazing\n- Part of Hatha Yoga and Kriya Yoga practices\n- Considered a cleansing (shatkarma) and concentration (dharana) technique\n\n2. Practice Methods:\n- Gazing at a candle flame\n- Focusing on a dot or point\n- Observing a yantra or mandala\n- Concentrating on the tip of the nose\n- Fixing eyes on a specific object without blinking\n\n3. Benefits:\n- Improves concentration and mental focus\n- Enhances eye strength and vision\n- Reduces eye strain\n- Calms the mind\n- Increases willpower\n- Helps control thoughts\n- Stimulates the pineal and pituitary glands\n- Aids in meditation practice\n\n4. Techniques:\n- External Trataka: Focusing on an external object\n- Internal Trataka: Visualizing an object with closed eyes\n\n5. Precautions:\n- Should be practiced under guidance\n- People with eye disorders should consult experts\n- Gradual practice is recommended\n\nTrataka is considered a powerful technique for mental discipline and spiritual growth.",
